                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1097.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Foreign office notifies to-day that by a decree dated 22, ports of Port de Paix,
                    Cape Haitien and Gonaives are blockaded and closed to foreign commerce. At
                    present it is a paper blockade as all Haitian war vessels at Port au Prince are
                    without coal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
